reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy and Functional
reviews.reviewText: This table was easy to put together and looks great in the room. My only advice is to be careful you don't tighten the screws too far or you might split the wood around the screw (totally my fault). I flipped a board over after I accidentally did this on one screw and it looks fine. Very sturdy and looks good in the room. My son loves the built in charging ports.

reviews.reviewText: I really love that this has outlets on the side for easy access for my teenager. He even put it together himself so easy assembly! It does seem a little short, that would be the only negative thing. Very happy with this purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easier than IKEA
reviews.reviewText: Living in an old house, electrical outlets are at a premium. And life in the modern age demands plugs and USB ports. I don't like surge protectors with multiple plugs because, I'm either a) stubbing my toe on the on button, leaving nothing protected (including my toe) or b) stumbling around in the dark when the alarm goes off, kicking the surge protector out of the wall. When I saw that this table had two outlets and A USB PORT, I purchased it. It arrived in a very small, flat box which I found, at first, intimidating. How could a table fit in this tiny box? Assembly could not have been easier. You have the option of a drill, a screwdriver or an enclosed Allen wrench. We all know how to use an Allen wrench. All like pieces were in their own numbered bags, in the order that they were needed. You put 1 and 2 (shelves) together first. You use bag 3 to secure 1 to 2. You righty-tighty the screws until they stop turning. The outlet/USB panel is the last to go. Total assembly time was maybe a half hour and the instructions were really helpful. It's also very Mission-style looking, very dark wood, which I like. It's the perfect height for charging your phone at night, for placing your alarm clock and for plugging in a lamp. I love it and would absolutely buy another one.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy little end table with plug ins
reviews.reviewText: I liked that it was packaged very well, all pieces were present, predrilled holes lined up, and it was easy to put together. It will be used as a bedside table to hold a phone and charge an emergency alert necklace.It is small so it works well in a studio apartment.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Get what you pay for
reviews.reviewText: Charging unit screws don’t hold so unit is not secured into table.
We have limited space but needed small end tables. These were perfect for what we wanted. Easy to assemble and they look great.

reviews.reviewTitle: Shockingly great tables for the price
reviews.reviewText: These little bedside tables really are unbelievable. For the price you really can’t beat these little tables. They take next to no time to set up, they feel sturdy, and the included outlets really do make these a step above similar products.These tables are a good height and fit nicely beside our bed without taking up too much space.My only negative for these would be that the outlets are a bit chunky. I kind of wish there was a nice piece of wood along the “backside” so that you could put them either way. Having the plug on the back would be a little more aesthetically pleasing. Otherwise, these are great.

reviews.reviewTitle: A little wobbly after a while, but otherwise awesome
reviews.reviewText: Quite like these! They look really good, and were pretty easy to install (although it definitely goes quicker if you have proper tools instead of using what's included). The only bad thing I have to say is they did get pretty wobbly after a while of having them, but for the price you pay they're pretty good I'd say! I especially like that you can plug things right into them instead of having a bunch of wires, definitely worth it if you're looking for some cheap bedside tables that'll get the job done and look good.

Easy to assemble. Purchased as needed a smaller nightstand for cabin. This set is perfect. Rustic brown, usb and plug at front is a bonus as minimal plugs in cabin bedroom. Highly recommend if need for smaller space.
Not to challenging to put together- fits perfectly in bedroom
